# jpcite — Cursor IDE auto-injection shim

> **Source of truth: `AGENTS.md`** at the repo root. Read it first.
> This file exists only so Cursor's auto-inject picks up a pointer.
> Last canonical edit: 2026-05-17 (Harness H3 — Agent Entry SOT shim).

## See `AGENTS.md`

All project identity, hard constraints, architecture, key commands, quality gates, and "what NOT to do" rules live in `AGENTS.md`. Do not duplicate or override them here.

For live counts (MCP tools / REST routes / OpenAPI paths / program counts) read `scripts/distribution_manifest.yml` or run `python scripts/probe_runtime_distribution.py`.

## Cursor-specific quirks

- Cursor sometimes auto-suggests `import anthropic` / `import openai` — these are **banned** under `src/`, `scripts/cron/`, `scripts/etl/`, `tests/` (see `AGENTS.md` constraint 3). If genuinely needed, place the file under `tools/offline/`.
- Cursor's "fix all" actions occasionally re-add a `tier-badge` CSS class or `Free tier` label — both are banned in user-facing copy (`AGENTS.md` constraint 1).
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones. Doubly so for `*.md` / `README*` (operator preference: no gratuitous docs).
- Default to MCP-first / API-first surfaces — jpcite has no UI value path.

## Companion shims

- `AGENTS.md` (root SOT) / `CLAUDE.md` (Claude shim) / `.agent.md` (vendor-neutral shim) / `.windsurfrules` (Windsurf shim) / `.mcp.json` (MCP client root config).
